# TaskManagerWpf — core standards

## Goal
- Keep the app **simple, deterministic, testable**.
- Prefer **clarity over cleverness**.

## Architecture (high level)
- WPF app uses **MVVM**.
- **Models**: pure data (`TaskItem`), no UI dependencies.
- **ViewModels**: state + commands + validation; no direct `MessageBox`/Window usage.
- **Views (XAML)**: bindings only; minimal code-behind (wiring/Initialize).
- **Services**: IO and UI bridges behind interfaces (`ITaskStore`, `IDialogService`, `IMessageService`).

## Quality gates
- Nullable reference types stay **enabled**; do not silence warnings without cause.
- Avoid hidden side effects: async methods accept `CancellationToken` when relevant.
- Errors are user-facing via `IMessageService`; **don’t swallow exceptions silently**.

## Changes policy
- Prefer **small PR-sized diffs**.
- Update/extend tests when behavior changes.
